The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Biman backs Buddha drive
                                                                                                            Biman backs Buddha drive
                            
	Calcutta, Jan. 4: CPM state secretary Biman Bose today supported the chief ministers resolve to industrialise Bengal despite the Oppositions efforts to derail it.         
	The peoples mandate in the last Assembly polls was in favour of industrialisation, he told a meeting of jute mill workers.        
	On the nearly 10,000-vote drop in the CPMs victory margin at Balagarh, Bose said: The peoples mood cannot be judged in a byelection.        
	Tram baby        
	A newborn boy was found abandoned in a tram tonight.        
	Tram company employees saw the child, wrapped in a towel, at the Ballygunge depot. Police said the tram arrived there from Kalighat around 9.                                                                                                                                                                             
